{"type":"message","id":"ebdbf68e","parentId":"828a3a58","timestamp":"2026-02-19T19:11:29.349Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing File Locations**\n\nI'm currently focused on the file paths. I've noted a potential discrepancy in the user's information: they mentioned `src/dmarket/api/market.py` while the task refers to `src/dmarket/api/client.py`. I'm checking if `get_market_items` is actually a method within a different class or module, to resolve the apparent misalignment.\n\n\n**Inspecting Module Inheritance**\n\nI am now closely examining the inheritance structure in `src/dmarket/api/market.py`. My assumption is that this module either inherits from or utilizes components from `client.py`. I'm specifically looking at how `BaseDMarketClient` is used and how the `_rust_client` is employed, given the user's instruction.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771528289346_101","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/dmarket/api/market.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":12181,"output":253,"cacheRead":9272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12434,"cost":{"input":0.024361999999999998,"output":0.003036,"cacheRead":0.0018544000000000002,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.029252399999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771528282139}}
{"type":"message","id":"410d35e0","parentId":"ebdbf68e","timestamp":"2026-02-19T19:11:29.367Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771528289346_101","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿\"\"\"Market operations for DMarket API.\"\"\"\r\n\r\nfrom typing import Any\r\n\r\nfrom src.dmarket.api.client import GAME_MAP\r\nfrom src.dmarket.api_validator import validate_response\r\nfrom src.dmarket.schemas import (\r\n    MarketItemsResponse,\r\n)  # Updated v2.0 schema  # Updated v2.0 schema\r\n\r\n\r\nclass MarketMixin:\r\n    \"\"\"Methods for interacting with DMarket marketplace.\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    @validate_response(MarketItemsResponse, endpoint=\"/exchange/v1/market/items\")\r\n    async def get_market_items(\r\n        self,\r\n        game: str = \"csgo\",\r\n        limit: int = 100,\r\n        offset: int = 0,\r\n        currency: str = \"USD\",\r\n        price_from: float | None = None,\r\n        price_to: float | None = None,\r\n        title: str | None = None,\r\n        sort: str = \"price\",\r\n        force_refresh: bool = False,\r\n        tree_filters: str | None = None,\r\n        cursor: str = \"\",\r\n    ) -> dict[str, Any]:\r\n        game_id = GAME_MAP.get(game.lower(), game)\r\n        params = {\r\n            \"gameId\": game_id,\r\n            \"limit\": limit,\r\n            \"offset\": offset,\r\n            \"currency\": currency,\r\n        }\r\n        if cursor:\r\n            params[\"cursor\"] = cursor\r\n        if price_from is not None:\r\n            params[\"priceFrom\"] = str(int(price_from * 100))\r\n        if price_to is not None:\r\n            params[\"priceTo\"] = str(int(price_to * 100))\r\n        if title:\r\n            params[\"title\"] = title\r\n        if sort:\r\n            params[\"orderBy\"] = sort\r\n        if tree_filters:\r\n            params[\"treeFilters\"] = tree_filters\r\n\r\n        return await self._request(\r\n            \"GET\",\r\n            \"/exchange/v1/market/items\",\r\n            params=params,\r\n            force_refresh=force_refresh,\r\n        )\r\n\r\n    async def get_suggested_price(\r\n        self, item_name: str, game: str = \"csgo\"\r\n    ) -> float | None:\r\n        response = await self.get_market_items(game=game, title=item_name, limit=1)\r\n        items = response.get(\"objects\", response.get(\"items\", []))\r\n        if not items:\r\n            return None\r\n        suggested = items[0].get(\"suggestedPrice\")\r\n        if isinstance(suggested, dict):\r\n            return float(suggested.get(\"amount\", 0)) / 100\r\n        return float(suggested) / 100 if suggested else None\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771528289365}}
