{"type":"message","id":"87120ea0","parentId":"ad0fd3c7","timestamp":"2026-02-19T19:19:18.869Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Integrating Market Item Fetching**\n\nI'm currently integrating `_fetch_market_items_rust` into the `BaseDMarket Client`. The plan is to place it strategically after the `_get_client` method. I've also considered defining `call_with_circuit_breaker` as a local wrapper to ensure smooth operation if the import fails. However, I need to check something before moving forward.\n\n\n**Implementing Rust Integration**\n\nI've added the `_fetch_market_items_rust` method to the `BaseDMarketClient`, positioning it to use the Rust client. The function will first check if the `rust_client` is initialized, providing a fallback. I've also wrapped the Rust call within a `try/except` block to handle potential issues, as suggested. After some consideration of edge cases, I believe this is an appropriate implementation of the method.\n\n\n**Implementing the Method**\n\nMy current plan involves adding the `_fetch_market_items_rust` method to the `BaseDMarketClient`, ensuring it follows `_get_client`. I'm making sure it uses the `rust_client` and wraps the Rust call in `asyncio.to_thread`. I will wrap the call to `call_with_circuit_breaker`. I've prepared a `try/except` block to handle potential errors and to raise `RequestFailed`.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771528758743_113","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"    async def _get_client(self) -> httpx.AsyncClient:\n        # Use a class-level singleton for the client to share the connection pool\n        if not hasattr(BaseDMarketClient, \"_shared_client\") or BaseDMarketClient._shared_client is None or BaseDMarketClient._shared_client.is_closed:\n            async with BaseDMarketClient._shared_client_lock:\n                # Double-check locking pattern\n                if not hasattr(BaseDMarketClient, \"_shared_client\") or BaseDMarketClient._shared_client is None or BaseDMarketClient._shared_client.is_closed:\n                    try:\n                        BaseDMarketClient._shared_client = httpx.AsyncClient(\n                            timeout=self.connection_timeout,\n                            limits=self.pool_limits,\n                            http2=self._http2_enabled,\n                            follow_redirects=True,\n                            verify=True,\n                        )\n                    except ImportError:\n                        self._http2_enabled = False\n                        BaseDMarketClient._shared_client = httpx.AsyncClient(\n                            timeout=self.connection_timeout,\n                            limits=self.pool_limits,\n                            http2=False,\n                            follow_redirects=True,\n                            verify=True,\n                        )\n        return BaseDMarketClient._shared_client\n\n    async def _fetch_market_items_rust(self, url: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Fetch market items using Rust client with circuit breaker.\"\"\"\n        if not self.rust_client:\n            raise RequestFailed(\"Rust client not initialized\")\n\n        async def _rust_call():\n            # Offload blocking Rust call to thread\n            try:\n                json_str = await asyncio.to_thread(self.rust_client.fetch_market_items, url)\n                return json_str\n            except Exception as e:\n                # Map rust error to something Python understands\n                raise RequestFailed(f\"Rust fetch failed: {e}\")\n\n        try:\n            # Use call_with_circuit_breaker as a wrapper function\n            json_str = await call_with_circuit_breaker(_rust_call)\n            return json.loads(json_str)\n        except Exception as e:\n            raise RequestFailed(e)\n","oldText":"    async def _get_client(self) -> httpx.AsyncClient:\n        # Use a class-level singleton for the client to share the connection pool\n        if not hasattr(BaseDMarketClient, \"_shared_client\") or BaseDMarketClient._shared_client is None or BaseDMarketClient._shared_client.is_closed:\n            async with BaseDMarketClient._shared_client_lock:\n                # Double-check locking pattern\n                if not hasattr(BaseDMarketClient, \"_shared_client\") or BaseDMarketClient._shared_client is None or BaseDMarketClient._shared_client.is_closed:\n                    try:\n                        BaseDMarketClient._shared_client = httpx.AsyncClient(\n                            timeout=self.connection_timeout,\n                            limits=self.pool_limits,\n                            http2=self._http2_enabled,\n                            follow_redirects=True,\n                            verify=True,\n                        )\n                    except ImportError:\n                        self._http2_enabled = False\n                        BaseDMarketClient._shared_client = httpx.AsyncClient(\n                            timeout=self.connection_timeout,\n                            limits=self.pool_limits,\n                            http2=False,\n                            follow_redirects=True,\n                            verify=True,\n                        )\n        return BaseDMarketClient._shared_client","file_path":"src/dmarket/api/client.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":28654,"output":1336,"cacheRead":25325,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29990,"cost":{"input":0.057308,"output":0.016032,"cacheRead":0.005065,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.078405}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771528741197}}
