{"type":"message","id":"1aab629f","parentId":"465643a5","timestamp":"2026-02-19T19:20:04.521Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Investigating Inheritance Issues**\n\nI'm currently trying to understand why the `MarketMixin` isn't directly inheriting from `BaseDMarketClient`, yet it's relying on `self.api_url` and `self._fetch_market_items_rust`, which are defined there. It seems like the code is working through an implicit assumption. I need to figure out how this connection is actually established.\n\n\n**Examining Error Handling Strategy**\n\nOkay, I've dug into the error handling. I see that the `_fetch_market_items_rust` method raises `RequestFailed` on failure, while the older Python code in `_request` returns a dictionary with an \"error\" key. This is a potential point of inconsistency. The caller, like `get_market_items`, may be expecting either a dictionary or an exception. Need to decide how best to unify the error responses.\n\n\n**Assessing Error Propagation**\n\nThe `MarketMixin` method's reliance on the Rust client and its potential for raising `RequestFailed` is being carefully examined.  I'm now tracing the error handling; `get_market_items`  is the main caller. This is crucial because `@validate_response` might change how errors are managed, which is important to consider. I must understand how exceptions interact with the response validation layer.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771528804516_116","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/dmarket/api_validator.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":30752,"output":543,"cacheRead":28280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31295,"cost":{"input":0.061503999999999996,"output":0.006516,"cacheRead":0.0056560000000000004,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.07367599999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771528787949}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce0d75fc","parentId":"1aab629f","timestamp":"2026-02-19T19:20:04.544Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771528804516_116","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\r\nУтилиты для валидации ответов DMarket API с помощью Pydantic схем.\r\n\r\nЭтот модуль предоставляет декораторы и функции для автоматической валидации\r\nответов API и отправки уведомлений при изменении формата API.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport logging\r\nfrom collections.abc import Callable\r\nfrom functools import wraps\r\nfrom typing import TYPE_CHECKING, Any, TypeVar\r\n\r\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, ValidationError\r\n\r\nif TYPE_CHECKING:\r\n    from src.telegram_bot.notifier import Notifier\r\n\r\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\r\n\r\nT = TypeVar(\"T\", bound=BaseModel)\r\n\r\n\r\nasync def send_api_change_notification(\r\n    endpoint: str,\r\n    validation_error: ValidationError,\r\n    response_data: dict[str, Any],\r\n    notifier: \"Notifier | None\" = None,\r\n) -> None:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Отправить критическое уведомление об изменении формата DMarket API.\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        endpoint: Эндпоинт API, который вернул невалидный ответ\r\n        validation_error: Ошибка валидации Pydantic\r\n        response_data: Данные ответа от API\r\n        notifier: Инстанс Notifier для отправки уведомлений\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    error_count = len(validation_error.errors())\r\n    first_errors = validation_error.errors()[:3]  # Первые 3 ошибки\r\n\r\n    error_details = \"\\n\".join([f\"- {err['loc']}: {err['msg']}\" for err in first_errors])\r\n\r\n    message = f\"\"\"\r\n🚨 КРИТИЧЕСКОЕ ИЗМЕНЕНИЕ DMarket API\r\n\r\n📍 Эндпоинт: {endpoint}\r\n❌ Ошибок валидации: {error_count}\r\n\r\nПервые ошибки:\r\n{error_details}\r\n\r\n⚠️ API DMarket изменился! Требуется обновление схем валидации.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    logger.critical(\r\n        \"API_SCHEMA_CHANGE_DETECTED\",\r\n        extra={\r\n            \"endpoint\": endpoint,\r\n            \"validation_errors\": error_count,\r\n            \"first_errors\": first_errors,\r\n            \"response_sample\": str(response_data)[:500],\r\n        },\r\n    )\r\n\r\n    # Отправляем уведомление, если доступен notifier\r\n    if notifier:\r\n        try:\r\n            await notifier.send_message(\r\n                message=message,\r\n                priority=\"critical\",\r\n                category=\"system\",\r\n            )\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            logger.exception(f\"Failed to send API change notification: {e}\")\r\n\r\n\r\ndef validate_response(  # noqa: UP047\r\n    schema: type[T],\r\n    endpoint: str = \"unknown\",\r\n) -> Callable:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Декоратор для автоматической валидации ответов API через Pydantic схемы.\r\n\r\n    При ValidationError:\r\n    - Логирует критическую ошибку\r\n    - Отправляет уведомление администраторам (если у instance есть notifier)\r\n    - Возвращает исходные данные без валидации\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        schema: Pydantic модель для валидации\r\n        endpoint: Название эндпоинта (для логирования)\r\n\r\n    Returns:\r\n        Декоратор функции\r\n\r\n    Example:\r\n        @validate_response(BalanceResponse, endpoint=\"/account/v1/balance\")\r\n        async def get_balance(self) -> dict[str, Any]:\r\n            ...\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n\r\n    def decorator(func: Callable) -> Callable:\r\n        @wraps(func)\r\n        async def wrapper(*args: Any, **kwargs: Any) -> dict[str, Any] | T:\r\n            # Вызываем оригинальную функцию\r\n            response_data = await func(*args, **kwargs)\r\n\r\n            # Если ответ содержит ошибку, не валидируем\r\n            if isinstance(response_data, dict) and response_data.get(\"error\"):\r\n                return response_data\r\n\r\n            # Пытаемся валидировать через схему\r\n            try:\r\n                schema.model_validate(response_data)\r\n                logger.debug(f\"API response validated successfully for {endpoint}\")\r\n                # Возвращаем исходные данные (dict) для backward compatibility\r\n                return response_data\r\n            except ValidationError as e:\r\n                # Критическая ошибка - формат API изменился!\r\n                logger.critical(\r\n                    f\"VALIDATION_FAILED for {endpoint}: {e}\",\r\n                    extra={\r\n                        \"endpoint\": endpoint,\r\n                        \"validation_error\": str(e),\r\n                        \"response\": response_data,\r\n                    },\r\n                )\r\n\r\n                # Получаем notifier из instance если доступен\r\n                notifier = None\r\n                if args and hasattr(args[0], \"notifier\"):\r\n                    notifier = args[0].notifier\r\n\r\n                # Отправляем уведомление асинхронно\r\n                try:\r\n                    await send_api_change_notification(\r\n                        endpoint=endpoint,\r\n                        validation_error=e,\r\n                        response_data=response_data,\r\n                        notifier=notifier,\r\n                    )\r\n                except Exception as notify_error:\r\n                    logger.exception(f\"Failed to send notification: {notify_error}\")\r\n\r\n                # Возвращаем невалидированные данные для backward compatibility\r\n                logger.warning(\r\n                    f\"Returning unvalidated data for {endpoint} due to validation failure\"\r\n                )\r\n                return response_data\r\n\r\n        return wrapper\r\n\r\n    return decorator\r\n\r\n\r\ndef validate_and_log(  # noqa: UP047\r\n    data: dict[str, Any],\r\n    schema: type[T],\r\n    endpoint: str = \"unknown\",\r\n) -> T | dict[str, Any]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Синхронная функция для валидации данных с логированием.\r\n\r\n    Используется когда декоратор не подходит (например, внутри метода).\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        data: Данные для валидации\r\n        schema: Pydantic модель\r\n        endpoint: Название эндпоинта (для логирования)\r\n\r\n    Returns:\r\n        Валидированная модель или исходные данные при ошибке\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    try:\r\n        validated = schema.model_validate(data)\r\n        logger.debug(f\"Data validated successfully for {endpoint}\")\r\n        return validated\r\n    except ValidationError as e:\r\n        logger.warning(\r\n            f\"Validation failed for {endpoint}: {e}\",\r\n            extra={\r\n                \"endpoint\": endpoint,\r\n                \"validation_error\": str(e),\r\n                \"data_sample\": str(data)[:200],\r\n            },\r\n        )\r\n        return data\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771528804542}}
